</paragraph>
<caption id="DF58C8BC7E62FFEEFF3F77B0DCA4FB4B" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677247" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3677247" box="[192,954,1178,1200]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677247/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" startId="16.[192,275,1178,1200]" targetBox="[192,1438,214,1144]" targetPageId="16">
<paragraph id="8B9898347E62FFEEFF3F77B0DCA4FB4B" blockId="16.[192,954,1178,1200]" box="[192,954,1178,1200]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="B95344267E62FFEEFF3F77B0DE31FB54" bold="true" box="[192,303,1178,1200]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">Figure 6.</emphasis>
Genomic trees of 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E62FFEEFE0B77B0DD45FB4B" box="[500,603,1178,1200]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Erynnini">Erynnini</taxonomicName>
. See Fig. 2 legend for notations.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B9898347E62FFEEFF3F77C2DC60F99A" blockId="16.[192,1440,1256,1633]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="B95344267E62FFEEFF3F77C2DE4DFAFB" bold="true" box="[192,339,1256,1280]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">Definition.</emphasis>
A likely sister genus to 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E62FFEEFD6B77C3DCE7FAFB" authority="Lindsey, 1925" authorityName="Lindsey" authorityYear="1925" box="[660,1017,1256,1280]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Potamanaxas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E62FFEEFD6B77C3DC25FAFB" box="[660,827,1257,1280]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">Potamanaxas</emphasis>
Lindsey, 1925
</taxonomicName>
, and thus not monophyletic with 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E62FFEEFF3F7622DEEAFADA" authority="Hubner, [1824]" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1824" box="[192,500,1288,1313]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Anastrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E62FFEEFF3F7622DE31FAE4" box="[192,303,1288,1311]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">Anastrus</emphasis>
H√ºbner, [1824]
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="549C26967E62FFEEFDFA7623DD25FADA" box="[517,571,1289,1313]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E62FFEEFD5B7622DB51FADA" authority="Hubner, [1824]" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1824" box="[676,1103,1288,1313]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Anastrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscurus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E62FFEEFD5B7622DC99FADB" box="[676,903,1288,1312]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">Anastrus obscurus</emphasis>
H√ºbner, [1824]
</taxonomicName>
), where these species were formerly placed (
<figureCitation id="131C84B17E62FFEEFE707602DECBFABB" box="[399,469,1320,1344]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="16.[192,275,1178,1200]" captionTargetBox="[192,1438,214,1144]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[192,1440,213,1144]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figure 6. Genomic trees of Erynnini. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677247" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677247/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). The need for this genus has been suggested previously (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6E5C57E62FFEEFB687602DA2FFABA" author="Austin" box="[1175,1329,1320,1345]" firstAuthor="Austin" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" pagination="19 - 25" refId="ref26322" refString="Austin, G. T. 1998. Hesperiidae of Rondonia, Brazil: Anastrus and Tosta, with descriptions of two new species (Lepidoptera: Hesperiidae: Pyrginae). Tropical Lepidoptera 9 (suppl. 2): 19 - 25." type="journal article" year="1998">Austin 1998</bibRefCitation>
). Keys to F.6.3. in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6E5C57E62FFEEFED77663DED4FA9B" author="Evans" box="[296,458,1352,1376]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" pagination="26 - 53" refId="ref27534" refString="Evans, W. H. 1953. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part III. Pyrginae. Section 2. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 246 p., pl. 26 - 53" type="book chapter" year="1953">Evans (1953)</bibRefCitation>
. Genitalia illustrated by Grishin in his fig. 30‚Äì39 (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6E5C57E62FFEEFBDE7662DBDDFA9A" author="Grishin" box="[1057,1219,1352,1377]" firstAuthor="Grishin" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" pagination="1 - 7" refId="ref27647" refString="Grishin, N. V. 2012. A new Central American Anastrus with unexpectedly distinct genitalia (Lepidoptera, Hesperiidae, Pyrginae). Tropical Lepidoptera Research 22 (1): 1 - 7." type="journal article" year="2012">Grishin 2012</bibRefCitation>
). Morphologically, distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E62FFEEFE507642DD00FA84" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1824" box="[431,542,1384,1407]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Anastrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E62FFEEFE507642DD00FA84" box="[431,542,1384,1407]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">Anastrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E62FFEEFDA47642DDCDFA7B" authority="" authorityName="" box="[603,723,1384,1408]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Echelatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E62FFEEFDA47642DDCDFA7B" box="[603,723,1384,1408]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">Echelatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having processes on sacculus of the valva and a second pair of uncus arms, from the ventral side of uncus, similar to some species of its sister 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E62FFEEFB0C76A3DA87FA5B" authorityName="Lindsey" authorityYear="1925" box="[1267,1433,1417,1440]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Potamanaxas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E62FFEEFB0C76A3DA87FA5B" box="[1267,1433,1417,1440]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">Potamanaxas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but uncus itself is essentially undivided with arms reduced to small knobs. Primary uncus arms are well-developed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E62FFEEFE6776E3DD20FA1B" authorityName="Lindsey" authorityYear="1925" box="[408,574,1481,1504]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Potamanaxas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E62FFEEFE6776E3DD20FA1B" box="[408,574,1481,1504]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">Potamanaxas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In facies, characterized by brown wings above with several dark-brown stripes and often with some bluish scaling between the stripes. Below, wings plain brown and some species with slate overscaling on the posterior third of hindwing. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly3570.7.4:A85T, aly3570.7.4:G86C, aly9673.2.5:T298A, aly 
<date id="FF99BEF47E62FFEEFB217502DA56F9BB" box="[1246,1352,1576,1600]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" value="1735-08-01">1735.8.1</date>
:C820C (not T), aly16.28.2:C88C (not A), aly16.28.2:A89A (not T).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33DCBBF7E62FFEEFF3F7552DCDBF8CA" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9898347E62FFEEFF3F7552DB8FF94B" blockId="16.[192,1440,1656,1712]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="B95344267E62FFEEFF3F7552DE45F96B" bold="true" box="[192,347,1656,1680]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is a masculine noun in the nominative singular, a group of species that were formerly placed in 
<emphasis id="B95344267E62FFEEFE5975B2DEC6F954" box="[422,472,1688,1711]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">Ana</emphasis>
[strus], but are phylogenetically closer to [Potamana] 
<emphasis id="B95344267E62FFEEFB9D75B3DB94F94B" box="[1122,1162,1689,1712]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">xas</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9898347E62FFEEFF3F75E2DE1CF8FB" blockId="16.[192,1440,1736,1793]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="B95344267E62FFEEFF3F75E2DEB4F91B" bold="true" box="[192,426,1736,1760]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">Species included.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="549C26967E62FFEEFE1D75E3DD08F91A" box="[482,534,1737,1761]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">type</typeStatus>
species, its sister 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E62FFEEFD1775E2DB59F91A" authority="Grishin, 2012" authorityName="Grishin" authorityYear="2012" box="[744,1095,1736,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Anastrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="isidro">
<emphasis id="B95344267E62FFEEFD1775E2DC81F91B" box="[744,927,1736,1760]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">Anastrus isidro</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6E5C57E62FFEEFC5B75E2DB59F91A" author="Grishin" box="[932,1095,1736,1761]" firstAuthor="Grishin" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" pagination="1 - 7" refId="ref27647" refString="Grishin, N. V. 2012. A new Central American Anastrus with unexpectedly distinct genitalia (Lepidoptera, Hesperiidae, Pyrginae). Tropical Lepidoptera Research 22 (1): 1 - 7." type="journal article" year="2012">Grishin, 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E62FFEEFB8075E2DFE5F8FA" authority="Moschler, 1877" authorityName="Moschler" authorityYear="1877" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pellicia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petius">
<emphasis id="B95344267E62FFEEFB8075E2DA38F91B" box="[1151,1318,1736,1760]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">Pellicia petius</emphasis>
M√∂schler, 1877
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9898347E62FFEEFF3F7432DCDBF8CA" blockId="16.[192,965,1816,1841]" box="[192,965,1816,1841]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="B95344267E62FFEEFF3F7432DE62F8CB" bold="true" box="[192,380,1816,1840]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">Parent taxon.</emphasis>
